by Karamiko » Sun Sep 13, 2020 3:47 pm

Miranda-22 is a mostly-functional space station on a Kuiper belt object orbiting an otherwise unremarkable red dwarf star. It is not under the jurisdiction of any planetary or interstellar government, making it a rather anarchic place where the only real authority on the station is Port Manager Price. In short, it feels like the kind of place where a young, suicidally overconfident, future starship captain would learn some life lessons by starting a near-lethal knife fight in a bar, while for everyone else it's just another Tuesday afternoon.

AN: The analogue of Russia in their universe's iteration of the Cold War appears to be something called the "Spartacist Union," which, although no more information is available on the subject, sounds like it would make for a very unusual and interesting take on an alternate USSR.

As a lot of time had passed, some of the languages spoken in Antarctica had been slightly altered.
For instance, the Antarctic Dravidian language uses the Kannada script, while its vocabulary is a blend of 4 real-life Dravidian languages spoken in India: Kannada, Tamil, Malayalam, and Telugu.
It's worth noting that the local version of the Mandarin Chinese did away with tones completely.
